iv>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isReflexiveEx","kind":"def","line":322,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.isReflexiveEx","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L322-L322"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isUnsafeEx\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">isUnsafeEx</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isUnsafeEx","kind":"def","line":321,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.isUnsafeEx","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L321-L321"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isRecEx\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">isRecEx</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isRecEx","kind":"def","line":320,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.isRecEx","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L320-L320"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.mkInductiveValEx\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkInductiveValEx</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">name</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">levelParams</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">type</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">numParams </span><span class=\"fn\">numIndices</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">all </span><span class=\"fn\">ctors</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">numNested</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">isRec </span><span class=\"fn\">isUnsafe </span><span class=\"fn\">isReflexive</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.mkInductiveValEx","kind":"def","line":304,"name":"Lean.mkInductiveValEx","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L304-L318"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.instInhabitedInductiveVal\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">instInhabitedInductiveVal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inhabited\">Inhabited</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.instInhabitedInductiveVal","kind":"instance","line":302,"name":"Lean.instInhabitedInductiveVal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L302-L302"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isReflexive\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">isReflexive</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"An inductive type is called reflexive if it has at least one constructor that takes as an argument a function returning the\nsame type we are defining.\nConsider the type:\n```\ninductive WideTree where\n| branch: (Nat -> WideTree) -> WideTree\n| leaf: WideTree\n```\nthis is reflexive due to the presence of the `branch : (Nat -> WideTree) -> WideTree` constructor.\n\nSee also: 'Inductive Definitions in the system Coq Rules and Properties' by Christine Paulin-Mohring\nSection 2.2, Definition 3\n","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isReflexive","kind":"def","line":300,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.isReflexive","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L300-L300"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isUnsafe\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">isUnsafe</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Whether the definition is flagged as unsafe. ","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isUnsafe","kind":"def","line":286,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.isUnsafe","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L286-L286"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isRec\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">isRec</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`true` when recursive (that is, the inductive type appears as an argument in a constructor). ","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.isRec","kind":"def","line":284,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.isRec","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L284-L284"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.numNested\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">numNested</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Number of auxiliary data types produced from nested occurrences.\nAn inductive definition `T` is nested when there is a constructor with an argument `x : F T`,\n where `F : Type → Type` is some suitably behaved (ie strictly positive) function (Eg `Array T`, `List T`, `T × T`, ...).  ","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.numNested","kind":"def","line":282,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.numNested","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L282-L282"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.ctors\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">ctors</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"List of the names of the constructors for this inductive datatype. ","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.ctors","kind":"def","line":278,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.ctors","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L278-L278"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.all\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">all</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"List of all (including this one) inductive datatypes in the mutual declaration containing this one ","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.all","kind":"def","line":276,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.all","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L276-L276"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.numIndices\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">numIndices</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Number of indices. An index is an argument that varies over constructors.\n\nAn example of this is the `n : Nat` argument in the vector constructor `cons : α → Vector α n → Vector α (n+1)`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.numIndices","kind":"def","line":274,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.numIndices","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L274-L274"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.numParams\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">numParams</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Number of parameters. A parameter is an argument to the defined type that is fixed over constructors.\nAn example of this is the `α : Type` argument in the vector constructors\n`nil : Vector α 0` and `cons : α → Vector α n → Vector α (n+1)`.\n\nThe intuition is that the inductive type must exhibit _parametric polymorphism_ over the inductive\nparameter, as opposed to _ad-hoc polymorphism_.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.numParams","kind":"def","line":269,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.numParams","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L269-L269"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.toConstantVal\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">toConstantVal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">InductiveVal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.ConstantVal\">ConstantVal</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.toConstantVal","kind":"def","line":261,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.toConstantVal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L261-L302"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.ConstantVal\">Lean.ConstantVal</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lean.Name</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lean.Name</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> → <a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\">Lean.InductiveVal</a></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal.mk","kind":"ctor","line":251,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L251-L302"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">InductiveVal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_extends\">extends</span> <span id=\"Lean.InductiveVal.toConstantVal\"><a href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.ConstantVal\">Lean.ConstantVal</a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The kernel compiles (mutual) inductive declarations (see `inductiveDecls`) into a set of\n- `Declaration.inductDecl` (for each inductive datatype in the mutual Declaration),\n- `Declaration.ctorDecl` (for each Constructor in the mutual Declaration),\n- `Declaration.recDecl` (automatically generated recursors).\n\nThis data is used to implement iota-reduction efficiently and compile nested inductive\ndeclarations.\n\nA series of checks are performed by the kernel to check whether a `inductiveDecls`\nis valid or not. ","docLink":"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.InductiveVal","kind":"structure","line":251,"name":"Lean.InductiveVal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Declaration.lean#L251-L302"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Declaration.html#Lean.Declaration.forExprM\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Declaration</span>.<span class=\"name\">forExprM</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn